Do we know who?
No confirmation,

16:24.609 --> 16:26.110
but it's
the place where Carlos
and Kiera were going.

16:31.032 --> 16:34.160
Oh, my God, Julian,
the detective is
hurt really badly.

16:34.244 --> 16:35.324
He needs a doctor.

16:35.412 --> 16:36.401
I know what he needs.

16:36.538 --> 16:39.405
We've got a dying cop...
You're holding us hostage...

16:40.542 --> 16:42.248
Is what you have in the barn
some kind of bomb?

16:42.377 --> 16:44.083
HOYT: Everybody, shut up!

16:45.088 --> 16:47.750
All right, here's how
this is gonna go down.
No one is gonna die.

16:48.466 --> 16:49.922
We're gonna tie you two up,

16:50.927 --> 16:52.918
and we're gonna quietly
make our way out
of here, all right?

16:53.054 --> 16:54.009
With a little luck,
someone will

16:54.097 --> 16:55.086
eventually come
looking for you.

16:55.265 --> 16:57.597
My partner is not
gonna make it that long.

16:58.768 --> 17:00.099
Julian,

17:00.437 --> 17:02.098
he needs a doctor.

17:02.480 --> 17:04.766
We'll call an
ambulance from a
payphone once we're gone.

17:06.985 --> 17:08.475
Our fight is with
the corporations.

17:10.655 --> 17:12.111
Fair enough.

17:13.783 --> 17:15.444
(SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE)

17:21.666 --> 17:22.997
I thought I said
to get their phones.
I did.

17:23.293 --> 17:24.783
Well, you
obviously missed a couple.

17:28.673 --> 17:30.755
What do we do now, Hoyt?
Give yourselves up.

17:33.803 --> 17:36.010
I'll tell them you didn't mean
to shoot Detective Fonnegra.

17:37.307 --> 17:38.763
I'll say that it
was an accident.

17:39.476 --> 17:40.636
(SIRENS WAILING)

17:42.020 --> 17:43.430
HOYT: Phil...

17:43.605 --> 17:44.845
I want you to go out
to the storage barn

17:45.023 --> 17:46.308
and keep watch
until I get there.

17:47.609 --> 17:49.099
I have a better idea...

17:49.194 --> 17:50.525
We start the revolution now.

17:58.536 --> 17:59.821
Ram the van into
the police barricade.

17:59.996 --> 18:01.281
We do Day One
right now, that's it.

18:01.373 --> 18:02.533
No, we need to escape.

18:03.333 --> 18:05.198
We're gonna make our statement
on our terms, not theirs.

18:07.045 --> 18:08.330
What's Day One?

18:09.631 --> 18:10.666
Theseus Day.

18:11.508 --> 18:13.874
He was a warrior
who unified the people
of Athens.

18:14.511 --> 18:16.502
He was also pushed off
a cliff when people
turned against him.

18:17.222 --> 18:19.178
Yeah, well some
challenges are worth the risk.

18:19.641 --> 18:22.724
I've seen thousands
of innocents killed
for a cause.

18:23.019 --> 18:24.555
Do you know what they
called the activists?

18:24.688 --> 18:25.803
DAN: Heroes?

18:27.023 --> 18:28.138
Murderers.

18:29.025 --> 18:30.640
lfyou want
your message heard,

18:31.403 --> 18:32.563
don't use violence.

18:32.696 --> 18:34.527
CARLOS: You guys
should turn yourselves in.

18:35.073 --> 18:36.734
Become celebrities.

18:36.866 --> 18:39.528
The police are
gonna have this place
surrounded within minutes.

18:39.661 --> 18:41.071
You cannot escape.

18:41.204 --> 18:43.035
No, they don't know
the place like I do.

18:44.040 --> 18:45.200
We can do this.

18:45.834 --> 18:48.371
I want spotters in place.
Cordon off the perimeter.

18:48.545 --> 18:50.536
Full sit-rep
briefing in 10 minutes.
You got it.

18:50.714 --> 18:53.706
Got two of mine inside,
Fonnegra and Cameron.

18:54.592 --> 18:56.423
You understand that
when a bomb is involved,

18:56.553 --> 18:58.885
public safety is top priority,
then officers on the scene.

18:59.097 --> 19:00.428
lfwe can't negotiate,
then we go in.

19:00.598 --> 19:02.008
Look, I know how this works.

19:02.559 --> 19:04.049
If it comes to that,

19:04.185 --> 19:06.050
just make sure your
team knows who's who.

19:09.024 --> 19:10.764
They're
beginning surveillance.

19:11.860 --> 19:13.725
What you need is a diversion.
HOYT: Shut up!

19:14.029 --> 19:15.018
No, she's right.

19:15.196 --> 19:16.185
Oh, good,
you're listening to her now.

19:16.281 --> 19:17.441
Just hear me out...

19:17.741 --> 19:19.402
We tell them we're
gonna detonate the bomb.

19:20.368 --> 19:21.824
Instead,
we blow up the propane tank.

19:21.911 --> 19:23.412
They're gonna
think that's the bomb.

19:23.621 --> 19:26.203
When they're looking
for the dead bodies,
we're gone through the woods.

19:26.291 --> 19:28.077
Except that we happen
to have five witnesses

19:28.251 --> 19:29.957
who know exactly
where we're going.

19:33.798 --> 19:34.913
No.

19:36.092 --> 19:37.468
We're not gonna kill them,

19:37.594 --> 19:39.050
that's not what we're about.

19:39.888 --> 19:41.753
You got a psychological
profile on this guy?

19:41.931 --> 19:43.512
My people are working on it.

19:43.600 --> 19:45.056
Do you have
a sense of their arsenal?

19:45.226 --> 19:46.636
Not yet.

19:52.108 --> 19:53.769
Is that all the guns?

19:54.110 --> 19:56.101
Looks about right.
That's not all of them.

19:57.489 --> 19:58.945
HOYT: What are you
talking about now, bitch?

19:59.449 --> 20:01.280
What did you say?

20:01.951 --> 20:03.236
Nothing.

20:03.953 --> 20:06.114
Hey, I got your dad's rat
pistol in my workshop.

20:07.332 --> 20:08.788
HOYT: Dan, go get it.

20:08.958 --> 20:10.164
Uh, he's never
gonna find it in there.

20:12.170 --> 20:14.126
All right, just
don't do anything stupid.

20:14.964 --> 20:16.124
Go with him.

20:18.968 --> 20:20.003
JULIAN: Gates!

20:22.097 --> 20:23.303
Go lock those
two in the pantry.

20:30.355 --> 20:32.937
Let them get used
to our presence,
then we'll make contact.

20:34.275 --> 20:35.481
Bradley...

20:36.486 --> 20:37.851
Randol's record is clean.

20:38.363 --> 20:40.604
Vickerdale
Enterprises bankrupted him
two years ago.

20:40.698 --> 20:42.484
He's been living on
his wife's property,

20:42.659 --> 20:44.365
holding anti-corporation
rallies since then.

20:44.494 --> 20:46.325
Clearly, he's escalated.

20:47.539 --> 20:48.870
Sir, we've got a sighting.

20:52.794 --> 20:54.455
Kids. He's using kids.

21:02.303 --> 21:05.010
Wow. First person shooter.

21:05.515 --> 21:06.550
(GUNSHOTS)

21:08.143 --> 21:10.885
Hey, stop!
Sorry, I'm just
checking my emails.

21:12.188 --> 21:14.895
Uh, I think the gun is behind
that suit somewhere.

21:18.361 --> 21:19.692
(GROANS)

21:21.406 --> 21:22.862
One for the good guys.

21:24.492 --> 21:25.993
KIERA: I have a plan.

21:26.161 --> 21:27.651
Yeah, you wanna
tell me what it is?

21:30.707 --> 21:31.742
Of course not.

21:39.841 --> 21:41.672
ALEC: Kiera?
Alec.

21:42.135 --> 21:43.215
What?

21:43.386 --> 21:45.377
I don't have much time.
They're expecting
me back soon.

21:45.722 --> 21:46.882
You've got me here.
What do you want me to do?

21:47.307 --> 21:49.047
Connect me to
Inspector Dillon.
Who are you talking to?

21:49.559 --> 21:50.799
Okay, just a second.

21:52.729 --> 21:54.185
Aw, come on.

21:54.647 --> 21:55.853
Did you patch me
through to their phone?

21:56.024 --> 21:57.230
Good and ready to go, sir.

21:58.860 --> 21:59.895
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

22:01.488 --> 22:02.568
This is Dillon.

22:04.073 --> 22:05.199
Bingo!
(DAN MOANS)

22:05.575 --> 22:06.690
Hello?

22:06.910 --> 22:08.741
Sir, it's Cameron.
Kiera?

22:09.245 --> 22:11.736
Bradley!
Hey, can we keep it down!

22:13.249 --> 22:15.911
Kiera, what's the situation?

22:16.044 --> 22:17.580
How many assailants?
Five.

22:18.171 --> 22:19.411
Armed with
handguns and shotguns.

22:20.048 --> 22:21.584
There are three hostages.
Two of them

22:21.758 --> 22:23.248
are in the kitchen.
One ofthem is in the barn.

22:23.384 --> 22:25.420
Carlos and l
are in the pantry,
and Carlos has been shot.

22:25.678 --> 22:26.929
DILLON: How bad?
KIERA: It’s not good.

22:27.430 --> 22:28.545
Listen,

22:29.098 --> 22:30.759
there's a bomb in
the storage barn.

22:31.017 --> 22:33.258
They are going to
explode the propane
tank as a diversion

22:33.895 --> 22:35.260
and escape through back roads.

22:37.273 --> 22:38.683
I'll have the chance
to take out the leader.

22:39.067 --> 22:41.274
Cameron, this is
ERT Commander Bradley.

22:41.402 --> 22:43.609
My team are in position,
let them do theirjob.

22:43.905 --> 22:45.520
Stand down,
keep your partner alive.

22:45.615 --> 22:47.571
KIERA:
With all due respect, sir.

22:48.076 --> 22:50.192
I am unwilling to
stand down because if
nothing is done,

22:50.745 --> 22:52.281
my partner dies.
BRADLEY: Cameron.

22:52.622 --> 22:54.032
Listen to me very carefully...

22:54.791 --> 22:57.954
The first priority
is to defuse that bomb
before Randol can detonate it.

22:58.086 --> 22:59.576
What's going on?
KIERA: No, sir...

23:01.256 --> 23:03.292
Hello?
Roland Randol is...
He's a hostage!

23:04.634 --> 23:05.965
She's gone.

23:07.136 --> 23:08.637
Hello? Sir?

23:09.472 --> 23:12.384
Wow, you really got
a good shock from that.

23:12.475 --> 23:15.467
Told you not to touch
that wire. You okay?

23:25.738 --> 23:26.898
Hey, what are you doing?

23:26.990 --> 23:29.402
Just getting more
towels for the bleeding cop.

23:29.659 --> 23:31.399
ls Cameron
gonna screw this up?

23:31.494 --> 23:32.995
I trust her instincts.

23:33.121 --> 23:34.657
Yeah, well the last
thing I need is a hothead

23:34.831 --> 23:36.321
running around,
getting people killed.

23:36.457 --> 23:37.663
She's not gonna be a problem.

23:38.585 --> 23:40.416
I hope you're right.

23:57.270 --> 23:59.431
Everything's gonna be okay.

24:00.523 --> 24:01.763
(BREATH ES HEAVILY)

24:01.858 --> 24:03.689
You're a lousy liar.

24:06.487 --> 24:10.696
Despite all the lies,
I still trust you.

24:12.160 --> 24:13.946
More than anyone.

24:14.829 --> 24:18.196
Although your name's
probably not even Kiera.

24:23.713 --> 24:25.829
My name is Kiera Cameron.

24:27.884 --> 24:30.125
l have a little
boy and a husband

24:30.219 --> 24:32.346
that I'm likely
to never see again.

24:35.224 --> 24:37.681
If I don't do everything
rightwhile I'm here,

24:38.186 --> 24:40.051
they may never exist.

24:44.233 --> 24:46.519
And the only friend I have...

24:49.405 --> 24:51.361
I lie to him every day.

24:53.368 --> 24:55.484
(WHISPERS) But I hate it.

24:56.913 --> 24:58.244
(SNIFFLES)

25:01.000 --> 25:02.240
I'm sorry, Carlos.

25:12.595 --> 25:14.836
Can I get this to the cops?

25:17.225 --> 25:20.012
Why are you
being so cooperative
all of a sudden, huh?

25:20.103 --> 25:23.436
You got the guns
and the manpower.
I'm not stupid.

25:23.606 --> 25:25.847
Drop it off, then come back.

25:28.236 --> 25:29.692
(DOOR OPENS)

25:32.198 --> 25:33.699
I think you can use these.

25:40.248 --> 25:42.284
Yeah, towels, thank you.

25:42.959 --> 25:44.369
Okay, then.

26:02.311 --> 26:04.723
(PHONE RINGING)

26:04.814 --> 26:05.974
Answer it.
Don't answer it!

26:06.065 --> 26:07.145
They're trying to help!

26:07.275 --> 26:08.310
(PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)

26:08.443 --> 26:10.729
Is anyone gonna
answer the phone?

26:10.820 --> 26:12.230
(PHONE RINGS)
(BEEP)

26:13.573 --> 26:14.733
Hello?

26:14.824 --> 26:16.564
Mr. Randol, are you there?

26:16.659 --> 26:17.739
Yes, I'm...

26:17.827 --> 26:18.816
(ANN GASPS)

26:25.960 --> 26:27.575
Yeah, yeah, I'm Roland Randol.

26:29.088 --> 26:31.579
Mr. Randol, this is
Martin Bradley of the VPD.

26:38.014 --> 26:39.595
Carlos?

26:39.849 --> 26:41.305
This is my plan.

26:45.354 --> 26:47.845
I'm gonna lead
them all outside

26:48.024 --> 26:50.515
and one by one,
I'm gonna pick 'em off.

26:56.324 --> 26:58.440
You're a good man, Carlos.

27:06.793 --> 27:08.954
(ELECTRONIC WHIRRING)

27:21.057 --> 27:25.050
You have hostages,
one ofthem hurt,
Carlos Fonnegra, how is he?

27:25.144 --> 27:26.133
He's alive.

27:36.864 --> 27:38.980
The others, are they okay?

27:39.200 --> 27:40.406
JULIAN:
Yeah, yeah, they're okay.

27:41.160 --> 27:43.321
Roland, can I call you Roland?

27:43.996 --> 27:46.408
I know what
happened with your farm,
I can only imagine...

27:46.499 --> 27:48.581
All right, enough chitchat!

27:48.668 --> 27:51.375
We are not afraid to die
to have our statement heard.

27:51.462 --> 27:53.043
Who's speaking now?
Mr. Randol?

27:56.384 --> 27:59.751
The world has turned its power
over to the corporations.

27:59.887 --> 28:01.923
We cry out for our
rights and no one listens.

28:02.265 --> 28:04.130
We voted against them,
nobody listens.

28:04.267 --> 28:05.473
The only way to
make people listen

28:05.601 --> 28:06.932
is to give our lives.
Hey.

28:07.061 --> 28:11.725
Wait, we're listening.
We've got TV crews,
we've got press, Internet.

28:11.816 --> 28:13.272
What the...

28:13.943 --> 28:15.479
(GROANS)

28:17.280 --> 28:20.647
If I see a cop
within 100 yards of
this place, I kill everyone!

28:20.783 --> 28:23.115
No, no, no, wait!
Nobody has to die.
Gates!

28:23.619 --> 28:24.825
Stay here.

28:24.996 --> 28:26.281
Tell us what we need to know.
Mr. Randol?

28:26.414 --> 28:27.494
(GUN SHOT FIRING)

28:27.623 --> 28:31.491
Mr. Randol!
Shots fired! All units, go!

28:34.130 --> 28:35.916
HOYT: You let them escape?
JULIAN:
What the hell happened?

28:36.007 --> 28:37.167
Damn it!
You okay?

28:37.300 --> 28:38.790
(BREATH ES HEAVILY)
We've got to find them.

28:38.926 --> 28:40.462
Ugh!
Hey, get up.

28:40.636 --> 28:42.092
You're coming with me.

28:46.475 --> 28:48.852
Stay with the hostages.

28:48.978 --> 28:51.185
No, Hoyt, stick to the plan!

28:54.859 --> 28:56.144
Bradley!

28:57.153 --> 28:58.313
BRADLEY: What the hell?

29:02.658 --> 29:03.818
Hoyt?

29:04.535 --> 29:06.150
Alec. Alec!
Alec!

29:06.287 --> 29:07.823
Hoyt? (PANTING)

29:08.039 --> 29:09.119
(GRUNTS)

29:11.542 --> 29:15.000
Okay, tie him up,
put him in the pantry,
get Dillon on the phone.

29:15.129 --> 29:16.960
Tell him the house is clear,
and when the EMTs get here,

29:17.048 --> 29:19.039
bring them to
Carlos immediately.
Okay.

29:19.175 --> 29:20.790
ROLAND: Alec, what's going on?

29:20.885 --> 29:22.170
I'm going after Hoyt.

29:26.807 --> 29:28.217
(FOOTSTEPS)

29:29.018 --> 29:30.883
Theseus!

29:31.020 --> 29:32.635
ERT OFFICER 1: Cover!

29:32.730 --> 29:34.266
Now! Take a shot.

29:42.990 --> 29:44.025
(GUNSHOTS FIRED)

29:44.200 --> 29:45.315
ERT OFFICER 2: Return fire!

30:01.676 --> 30:04.088
We ’ve got
gunfire being exchanged
on the northeast corner

30:04.220 --> 30:05.630
and a sniper in
the storage barn.

30:06.013 --> 30:08.345
The bomb is in the barn.
A stray shot could set it off.

30:08.432 --> 30:10.218
Hold fire on that position
unless you can
get a clean shot.

30:10.351 --> 30:11.386
Roger.

30:11.519 --> 30:12.929
ljust got a phone
call from someone

30:13.104 --> 30:14.344
inside the house
claiming the house is clear.

30:14.563 --> 30:16.599
Get your team to the house,
see ifyou can
recover the hostages.

30:16.857 --> 30:18.233
Roger that.

30:22.238 --> 30:24.229
REPORTER:
We have now confirmed,

30:24.407 --> 30:26.443
a militant group
headed up by Roland Rando/

30:26.575 --> 30:28.566
have taken
hostages on a Surrey farm.

30:28.703 --> 30:29.863
SONYA: What's going on?

30:30.037 --> 30:31.243
Theseus.

30:33.374 --> 30:34.409
It's started.

30:34.583 --> 30:37.199
REPORTER: ERT are on
the scene and we’ve had
reportings of gunfire.

30:37.294 --> 30:38.909
We’ll have more as
the story develops.

30:39.046 --> 30:41.628
Well, isn't there
something we should do?
They could kill him.

30:41.924 --> 30:43.585
No, don't worry.

30:44.719 --> 30:48.712
Everything I am,
everything I become

30:49.932 --> 30:54.676
will be
the result of events
unfolding on that farm.

31:12.329 --> 31:13.660
ERT OFFICER 3: Get back!

31:14.123 --> 31:15.954
(INDISTINCT TALKING)

31:20.296 --> 31:21.456
Ugh!

31:35.811 --> 31:37.142
(SIGHS)

31:42.359 --> 31:43.815
ERT OFFICER 4:
Move, move, let's go!

31:48.491 --> 31:49.981
ROLAND: Alec, quick!

31:53.496 --> 31:54.986
Get your mom.

31:55.664 --> 31:57.700
(EXCLAIMS)
ANN: Oh, my God!

31:58.125 --> 31:59.786
Get your mom.
Oh, my God.

32:03.172 --> 32:04.912
Check that those
back roads are covered.

32:05.007 --> 32:06.292
Where are we on the hostages?

32:06.383 --> 32:08.339
Approaching the house.

32:10.179 --> 32:11.669
ERT OFFICER 5: Move, move!
ERT OFFICER 6: Go, go!

32:15.726 --> 32:18.308
What are you doing here?
You said you were gonna leave.

32:18.395 --> 32:20.101
(PANTING) I came
back to get you.

32:20.189 --> 32:21.895
What? Are you
gonna take him hostage?

32:22.024 --> 32:23.639
(PANTING) I'm
here to help you.

32:24.401 --> 32:26.653
If the cops find you
they're not gonna
let you go, Dad.

32:28.072 --> 32:30.984
Son, look at me. Look at me.

32:32.201 --> 32:35.819
Listen to me.
Just listen, okay?

32:39.834 --> 32:42.541
Listen, ifyou want
me to come with you,
I'll come, okay?

32:42.670 --> 32:44.376
(BREATH ES HEAVILY)

32:45.214 --> 32:47.705
I'm beggin' you,
don't do this. Don't!

32:47.925 --> 32:49.165
Get out of the way.

32:51.720 --> 32:52.846
GATES: Hey!

32:53.055 --> 32:54.295
What?
Let's make a break for it.

32:54.390 --> 32:57.757
You go, coward.
We didn't build
a bomb for nothing.

33:02.606 --> 33:04.062
Don't move!

33:10.781 --> 33:13.739
Put the gun down,
turn yourself in.

33:15.244 --> 33:16.984
You know that's
the only way this ends.

33:17.079 --> 33:18.910
I... I'm warning you!

33:20.958 --> 33:22.573
(GUNSHOT FIRED)

33:28.257 --> 33:30.373
It just went off.

33:45.983 --> 33:47.473
Julian...

33:47.610 --> 33:48.941
OFFICER ON LOUDSPEAKER:
This is the VPD.

33:49.111 --> 33:50.442
Put your
weapons down and come out!

33:52.656 --> 33:54.738
Alpha one,
Tango's in the house.

33:56.452 --> 33:58.067
Positive ID, Randol.

33:59.580 --> 34:01.741
(BREATH ES HEAVILY)

34:01.957 --> 34:04.824
You made your statement, Son.

34:05.794 --> 34:08.410
I understand, God! (SIGHS)

34:09.340 --> 34:11.831
You came back to
save me and I will
stand beside you,

34:11.967 --> 34:14.344
I swear to God lwill, but...

34:19.475 --> 34:21.807
(SIGHS) It's over, Son.

34:22.603 --> 34:24.594
There's nowhere to run.

34:28.484 --> 34:30.099
It's over, Son.

34:30.527 --> 34:32.438
I love you, but please.
No.

34:32.529 --> 34:33.985
Please.
No.

34:35.532 --> 34:36.817
Please.

34:37.326 --> 34:38.816
I'm so sorry.

34:40.162 --> 34:42.118
I'm so, so sorry.
No.

34:42.706 --> 34:44.697
It's all my fault.
No.

34:46.335 --> 34:48.041
